hi. From 20th  December 2017 to 28 February 2018.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pib.gov.in/Pressreleaseshare.aspx?PRID=1537599|title=\"Dhanraj Bhagat (1917-1988): Journey from the Physical to the Spiritual\", Exhibition Inaugurated at NGMA, Mumbai|website=pib.gov.in|access-date=2019-10-28}}</ref>\n\n=== Exhibition list of NGMA from 1985 ===\n\n* \"Graphics of the 70\u2019s Federal Republic of Germany\" at National Gallery of Modern Art, New Delhi,1985.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ngmaindia.gov.in/virtual-gallery-contemporary-fedaral.asp|title=National Gallery of Modern Art, New Delhi|website=ngmaindia.gov.in|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref>\n* \"Henry Moore: Sculptures, Drawings & Graphics\" at National Gallery of Modern Art, New Delhi, from 1 October to 15 November 1987.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ngmaindia.gov.in/virtual-gallery-henry-moore-sculptors.asp|title=National Gallery of Modern Art, New Delhi|website=ngmaindia.gov.in|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref>\n* \"Indian Women Sculptors in Celebration of International Women's Day\" at National Gallery of Modern Art, New Delhi from 2 to 29 March 1987.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ngmaindia.gov.in/virtual-gallery-indian-women-sculptors.asp|title=National Gallery of Modern Art, New Delhi|website=ngmaindia.gov.in|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref>\n* \"Thresholds: Contemporary French Art\" at National Gallery of Modern Art, New Delhi,1995.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ngmaindia.gov.in/virtual-gallery-contemporary-french-art.asp|title=National Gallery of Modern Art, New Delhi|website=ngmaindia.gov.in|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref>\n* \"The Self and the world An Exhibition of Indian Women Artists\" at National Gallery of Modern Art, New Delhi from 5 to 30 April 1997.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://ngmaindia.gov.in/virtual-gallery-women-artists.asp|title=National Gallery of Modern Art, New Delhi|website=ngmaindia.gov.in|access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref>\n* \"Indian Contemporary Art, from the Collection of the National Gallery of Modern Art, New Delhi